y quincey noted the company is in a period of substantial transformation and change that is never easycocacolas efforts to adapt have included marketing drinks that are seen as healthier and pledging to reduce its sugar footprint its also cutting costs and refranchising bottling and distribution operations in north america a move that focuses the company more squarely on marketing and brand building play video cbs evening news americas first soda faces closure after countrys first soda tax del conners family has been in the soda business for over  years but after philadelphia passed its sugary drink tax dr physicks a pure  in north america cocacola said sales volume was even during the quarter reflecting slightly positive growth in carbonated drinks such as sprite and growth in juice and dairy volume for water enhanced water and sports drinks declined the company saidfor the three months ended june  coke earned  billion or  cents per share that compares with  billion or  cents per share a year earlierearnings adjusted for onetime costs were  cents per share thats better than the  cents per share analysts surveyed by zacks investment research called forrevenue for the atlanta company declined to  billion from  billion hurt by the ongoing refranchising of bottling territories and foreign currency fluctuations analysts expected  billion in revenue according to zackscocacola anticipates fullyear earnings per share will be flat to down  percent from the prior years  per share its previous outlook was for the results to be down  percent to  percentcocacola stock lost  cents  percent to  before the market opened wednesday   the associated press all rights reserved this material may not be published broadcast rewritten or redistributed comment share tweet stumble email featured in moneywatch  of the coolest places to retire in the world find out what activities and attractions make these  cities and town some of the best places to retire around the world  products you shoul